column5: about 15 years ago my wife and I stayed at a camp on Ena Lake near the English River not far from Kenora. Nice lake, nice older couple ran it. Great fishing. Does anyone know if it still exists? Trail
No, it's closed. Greetings from the Ena Lake
I went to Camp Ena for many years. The biggest draw is Vermillion Lake. Wish I could spend a day out there again (and you can from other camps), but we found a place that is just too good
If I remember right, it was Ray and Gloria Paul. First few Canada trips I stayed there. Great memories and good people.
